			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Under NaCl it is possible to create a shared memory FD with
imc_mem_obj_create(size).  This returns a FD with read+write
permissions.

It would be useful to be able to create a read-only version of this
FD, in order to follow the Principle of Least Authority when passing
FDs to other processes that don't need write access.  However, NaCl
currently provides no operation for doing this.
